body: The logic previously added for type deduction involving forwarding references breaks down in some situations when we have other overloads. This PR fixes that.

comment_data.body: I moved this logic to inside `best_match`, so that we don't "permanently" alter the argument types.
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -5784,18 +5784,8 @@ def analyse_c_function_call(self, env):
             else:
                 alternatives = overloaded_entry.all_alternatives()
 
-            # For any argument/parameter pair A/P, if P is a forwarding reference,
-            # use lvalue-reference-to-A for deduction in place of A when the
-            # function call argument is an lvalue. See:
-            # https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/template_argument_deduction#Deduction_from_a_function_call
-            arg_types = [arg.type for arg in args]
-            if func_type.is_cfunction:
-                for i, formal_arg in enumerate(func_type.args):
-                    if formal_arg.is_forwarding_reference():
-                        if self.args[i].is_lvalue():
-                            arg_types[i] = PyrexTypes.c_ref_type(arg_types[i])
-
-            entry = PyrexTypes.best_match(arg_types, alternatives, self.pos, env, args)
+            entry = PyrexTypes.best_match([arg.type for arg in args],

comment_data.body: `args` could be `None` here, so I'm not 100% sure about this fix...
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -4599,12 +4599,22 @@ def best_match(arg_types, functions, pos=None, env=None, args=None):
             errors.append((func, error_mesg))
             continue
         if func_type.templates:
+            # For any argument/parameter pair A/P, if P is a forwarding reference,
+            # use lvalue-reference-to-A for deduction in place of A when the
+            # function call argument is an lvalue. See:
+            # https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/template_argument_deduction#Deduction_from_a_function_call
+            arg_types_for_deduction = arg_types.copy()
+            if func.type.is_cfunction and args:

comment_data.body:
Let's keep this simple.
```suggestion
            arg_types_for_deduction = list(arg_types)
```

             errors.append((func, error_mesg))
             continue
         if func_type.templates:
+            # For any argument/parameter pair A/P, if P is a forwarding reference,
+            # use lvalue-reference-to-A for deduction in place of A when the
+            # function call argument is an lvalue. See:
+            # https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/template_argument_deduction#Deduction_from_a_function_call
+            arg_types_for_deduction = copy.copy(arg_types)

commit.message: Fix type deduction logic for forwarding reference argument
Check that args is not None
Use copy.copy() instead of copy method
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/cython/cython into fix-rvalue-ref-deduction
